# A named reference to a pattern-matched function should still feed the
# activation's argument proof into the matcher decision tree. The source is
# total via a catch-all, but the two observed activations select only `:left`
# and `:right`; the catch-all is dead and must not contribute `:other`.
#
# Expected: main() : {:one, :two}; the catch-all is source-total but dead for
# the observed activations.

fn pick(:left), do: :one
fn pick(:right), do: :two
fn pick(_), do: :other

fn main() do
  f = &pick/1
  {f.(:left), f.(:right)}
end
